<p class="courseblocktitle"><strong>ARCH&#160;23210.  Urban Core in Paris.  100 Units.</strong></p><p class="courseblockdesc">
This course is both an introduction to how historians think about cities and a history of cities from the Middle Ages through the Cold War. Most of the examples are drawn from Europe, with a special focus for the version of the course taught in Paris on that city, but significant attention is given to Africa and the United States. The course is chronological in organization, but each class also focuses on a different theme, such as the place of politics, industrial development, migration, culture, and commerce in the transformation of urban forms and experiences.</p><p class="courseblockdetail">
